cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on reducing energy consumption in mobile devices for LTE and 5G standards, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes and compares two machine learning approaches for predictive power management. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses dynamic power management as an integral part of contemporary hardware design. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses improving power efficiency through structural and technological advances. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses using information from the environment and communication protocol to make proactive decisions for power management.
